body:
hi Clifford,
you seemed to have fixed one such case, here is another one:      
verilog file contains two outputs while the produced AIGER has only one.      
Verilog:
```
module model(cancel, req, grant, ack);

input cancel;
input req;

output grant;
output ack;

reg [0:0] __m;

wire grant;
wire ack;

assign grant = ((cancel==0) && (__m==0) && (req==0)) || ((cancel==1) && (__m==0) && (req==0)) || ((cancel==1) && (__m==0) && (req==1)) || ((cancel==0) && (__m==0) && (req==1));
assign ack = ((cancel==0) && (__m==0) && (req==0)) || ((cancel==1) && (__m==0) && (req==0)) || ((cancel==1) && (__m==0) && (req==1)) || ((cancel==0) && (__m==0) && (req==1));

initial begin
__m = 0;
end

always@($global_clock)
begin
if (((cancel==0) && (__m==0) && (req==0))) __m <= 0;
else if (((cancel==1) && (__m==0) && (req==0))) __m <= 0;
else if (((cancel==1) && (__m==0) && (req==1))) __m <= 0;
else if (((cancel==0) && (__m==0) && (req==1))) __m <= 0;
end
endmodule
```

The translation script I use is:
```
read_verilog ./missing_outs.v
synth -flatten -top model
abc -g AND
write_aiger -ascii -symbols ./missing_outs.aag
```
The produced AIGER misses one output in the header and its definition:
```
aag 3 2 1 1 0
2
4
6 6
7
i0 cancel
i1 req
l0 __m
o0 ack grant
c
Generated by Yosys 0.7+214 (git sha1 621787a, clang 3.8.0-2ubuntu4 -fPIC -Os)
```
(it also renames output to combined `ack grant` but that I can, in principle, workaround by post-processing)

